org.testah.driver.web.element

Class AbstractWebElementWrapper

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.testah.driver.web.element.AbstractWebElementWrapper
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    WebElementWrapperV1

    public abstract class AbstractWebElementWrapper
extends java.lang.Object
    The Class AbstractWebElementWrapper is designed to wrap Webdriver WebElements and provide for more macrotized methods and chaining for less code in tests.

      • waitTillGone

        public AbstractWebElementWrapper waitTillGone()
        Wait till gone will wait up to the timeout, default value pulled from Testah properties, for the element to no longer be found or be displayed. Types of usecases where this would be called is if clicking a close button, and wait for it to go away before moving forward.

        Once timeout is exceeded or the element is not found or not displated an assert will be triggered since this methods assumes you want it to no longer to be found.

        Returns:
        the abstract web element wrapper

      • waitTillGone

        public AbstractWebElementWrapper waitTillGone(int timeout)
        Wait till gone will wait up to the timeout for the element to no longer be found or be displayed. Types of usecases where this would be called is if clicking a close button, and wait for it to go away before moving forward.

        Once timeout is exceeded or the element is not found or not displated an assert will be triggered since this methods assumes you want it to no longer to be found.

        Parameters:
        timeout - the timeout
        Returns:
        the abstract web element wrapper
